comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-31T19:26:09.188Z",audit-telemetry-agent,"Phase 1 complete: read all 5 source files (consent.ts, runtime.ts, observability.ts, instrument.ts, helpers.ts), health.ts (1530 LOC), validate.ts (structure). Dedup searches done for 12 query dimensions. Findings so far: (1) Sentry tracesSampleRate=0.2 (pm-wvhs closed); (2) telemetry source_context has audit_smoke but no dedicated pm telemetry query command; (3) validate has no --fix mode; (4) health advisory/blocking split is solid; (5) tracing to SLO alerting codified in Sentry dashboard - not in repo. Proceeding to final gap analysis."
  "2026-05-31T19:28:35.976Z",audit-telemetry-agent,"Phase 2 complete. All 7 source files read and linked. Key findings: (1) schema_version=1 hard-coded, no upgrade path ADR; (2) health remediation only in extensions triage, not other checks; (3) validate has remediation_hints only for resolution missing-fields, not other check types; (4) no pm telemetry local-query command (pm cakn was 'analyze persisted telemetry' but that was remote skill, not local CLI cmd); (5) Sentry instrument.ts has 44 scrub calls covering all event paths well; (6) tracesSampleRate=0.2 is correct (pm-wvhs closed); (7) TELEMETRY_MAX_QUEUE_ENTRY_ATTEMPTS=15 with exponential backoff up to 1hr cap is sound; (8) advisory/blocking split in isAdvisoryHealthWarning() is well-guarded. Proceeding to write final output."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-31T19:28:00.271Z",audit-telemetry-agent,"Telemetry event schema is pinned at schema_version=1 (runtime.ts:25) with no migration path or version-negotiation in ingest endpoint — if server-side parsing evolves, old queued events will silently mismatch. Gap: no ADR or forward-compat story for schema_version>1."
  "2026-05-31T19:28:02.987Z",audit-telemetry-agent,"health.ts remediation strings are only present inside checks[name=extensions].details.triage.remediation; all other check types (telemetry, integrity, history_drift, vectorization) emit only warning-code strings with no machine-readable fix_command map. Agents must infer remediation from codes. Gap: structured remediation_map per warning-code across all check types."
